WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:02.195
(Irisa, voice-over)
Previously on <i>Defiance...</i>

00:02.231 --> 00:05.596
I don't believe Rahm Tak
will ever release Alak alive.

00:06.295 --> 00:07.845
Ugh!

00:10.049 --> 00:11.966
A fully functional
Omec warship

00:12.051 --> 00:14.385
could destroy the entire
Votanis Collective.

00:14.553 --> 00:16.471
T'evgin needs to die.

00:16.555 --> 00:19.607
So long as that mad man
has the power to expose us,

00:19.725 --> 00:21.642
we must obey his commands.

00:21.777 --> 00:22.944
Is that poison?

00:23.062 --> 00:25.146
I'll fill a hidden needle,

00:25.230 --> 00:28.066
and inject the Omec
during coitus.

00:28.200 --> 00:29.534
Why do you want me dead?

00:29.618 --> 00:32.070
Actually, I don't.

00:32.204 --> 00:33.654
I need to know
I can count on you.

00:33.739 --> 00:35.823
(Nolan) You had him,
and if you hadn't have choked,

00:35.958 --> 00:37.909
Rahm Tak would be
a cooling corpse right now,

00:38.043 --> 00:39.711
and Defiance would be
a whole lot safer.

00:39.845 --> 00:41.079
- You're benched.
- Nolan!

00:41.246 --> 00:42.547
You're gonna stay here
with Berlin,

00:42.664 --> 00:44.248
you're gonna figure out
who planted those explosives.

00:44.383 --> 00:46.084
I'm the lawkeeper now.

00:46.168 --> 00:47.085
[impact]

00:47.219 --> 00:48.086
[panting]

00:48.170 --> 00:49.420
Ugh!

00:49.555 --> 00:51.723
- Oh!
- Nolan...

00:51.807 --> 00:53.057
[winces]

00:53.175 --> 00:54.792
[choking]

00:54.927 --> 00:56.661
Ugh!
Oh...

00:56.762 --> 00:59.013
Whatever's inside
this man's head is killing him!

00:59.148 --> 01:02.016
[rapid breathing]

01:04.319 --> 01:07.238
[pleasant music]

01:07.356 --> 01:13.911
♪ ♪

01:13.996 --> 01:15.329
It doesn't look broken.

01:15.447 --> 01:17.165
It'll be fine.

01:17.282 --> 01:19.117
Here, this will help
soak up the blood.

01:19.251 --> 01:22.587
- Thanks.
- Oh, gross, gross, gross.

01:22.704 --> 01:23.955
Is it working?

01:24.123 --> 01:25.873
- Pretty much.
- Did you hit him back?

01:25.958 --> 01:27.291
Are you kidding?

01:27.426 --> 01:29.010
What is wrong
with you?

01:29.128 --> 01:30.711
He's the biggest kid
in the yard.

01:30.796 --> 01:33.881
I hit back,
he hits me twice.

01:33.966 --> 01:35.550
It's safer just
to fall down.

01:35.634 --> 01:38.269
I didn't raise you
to be a doormat.

01:38.387 --> 01:40.972
Oh, so you raised me?

01:41.106 --> 01:43.191
Don't tell Mom and Dad.

01:43.308 --> 01:45.393
[rumbling in the distance]

01:45.544 --> 01:48.045
Look!
It's the aliens!

01:48.147 --> 01:50.031
(Rebecca)
Get away from the window.

01:50.182 --> 01:51.115
It's okay.

01:51.200 --> 01:53.734
Jon Stewart says
they're friendly.

01:53.819 --> 01:56.737
[whooshing and rattling]

01:59.758 --> 02:00.658
[gasps]

02:00.793 --> 02:02.326
- Watch out!
- Ah.

02:02.494 --> 02:04.378
She's got it.

02:04.496 --> 02:06.881
Josh, help me put this stuff
back where it was.

02:06.999 --> 02:08.216
How did you know?

02:08.333 --> 02:10.050
'Cause that's
my sister, Rebecca.

02:10.169 --> 02:12.336
- No, everything looks fine.
- Did anything break?

02:12.471 --> 02:14.422
(Nolan)
And that little boy is me.

02:14.556 --> 02:15.840
Just put the stuff anywhere.

02:16.008 --> 02:17.475
- No.
- Where are we?

02:17.593 --> 02:19.477
(Rebecca) Everything needs to go
back where it was.

02:19.561 --> 02:20.878
You know how OCD...

02:22.014 --> 02:24.515
[machine beeping]

02:24.650 --> 02:26.067
How long has he been like this?

02:26.185 --> 02:27.485
Hour, hour-and-a-half.

02:27.569 --> 02:29.103
We stopped to refuel
and he just collapsed.

02:29.238 --> 02:30.188
[gurgling]

02:30.322 --> 02:32.824
We need to sedate him!
Top drawer, behind you!

02:32.908 --> 02:35.193
You've got some moves, kid.
You a doctor?

02:35.327 --> 02:36.360
Veterinarian.

02:36.528 --> 02:37.829
[groaning]

02:37.913 --> 02:39.664
I'll take it.
There's a crash cart behind you.

02:39.748 --> 02:40.915
Grab it in case we need
to defibrillate.

02:41.033 --> 02:41.999
I'm on it.

02:42.117 --> 02:43.084
What's wrong with him?

02:43.202 --> 02:45.786
No clue.
But we're losing him.

02:45.921 --> 02:47.071
[gurgling]

02:49.474 --> 02:51.676
Do you think we're dead?

02:51.777 --> 02:53.578
I don't feel dead.

02:56.715 --> 03:00.184
No.

03:00.269 --> 03:03.054
This is something else.

03:03.222 --> 03:05.556
You never said
you had a sister.

03:07.893 --> 03:11.195
[explosions]

03:11.330 --> 03:14.966
[gunfire]

03:15.100 --> 03:16.467
[explosions]

03:16.568 --> 03:18.653
[shouting]

03:18.787 --> 03:21.656
[gunfire]

03:26.578 --> 03:28.713
Rebecca?

03:28.830 --> 03:30.581
Josh, you gotta be careful
with those rounds.

03:30.716 --> 03:31.916
They're explosive tipped.

03:32.000 --> 03:33.751
I know what I'm doing,
I trained on the T9s.

03:33.835 --> 03:36.053
Hey, look at me.
Focus.

03:36.171 --> 03:37.755
You're scared and
you'd piss yourself

03:37.890 --> 03:39.090
if you weren't so exhausted.

03:39.224 --> 03:41.175
So am I.

03:41.310 --> 03:43.144
But Cooper's unit's coming
through here tomorrow

03:43.262 --> 03:45.422
and they're gonna need this ammo
we're guarding, okay?

03:45.458 --> 03:47.135
- [explosions]
- I know, I know.

03:47.171 --> 03:48.866
Hey.
Those were empty coffins

03:48.902 --> 03:50.662
at Mom and Dad's funerals.
Why?

03:50.736 --> 03:51.669
You have to bring this up?

03:51.770 --> 03:52.987
They were vaporized.

03:53.105 --> 03:55.106
And we lost our parents.

03:55.240 --> 03:56.941
I want payback,
don't you?

03:57.109 --> 03:58.359
Yeah.
Yes.

03:58.493 --> 04:00.945
We're Nolans.
We have one rule.

04:01.079 --> 04:02.847
We live together...

04:02.948 --> 04:05.116
Or we die together.

04:05.284 --> 04:06.834
Good man.

04:06.952 --> 04:09.837
[gunfire and explosions]

04:12.090 --> 04:13.874
(Rebecca)
They're getting on the roof!

04:13.959 --> 04:16.127
I remember this.

04:18.463 --> 04:20.964
[explosions]

04:21.132 --> 04:21.966
No!

04:22.134 --> 04:23.351
[gunfire]

04:23.468 --> 04:25.937
I got incoming!
Take out the I-rat!

04:26.021 --> 04:26.971
[grunts]

04:27.168 --> 04:29.983
_

04:30.068 --> 04:31.771
_

04:32.227 --> 04:34.979
No... more... fight.

04:35.147 --> 04:37.865
C'mon Josh, waste him
and get over here!

04:37.983 --> 04:40.568
Listen to her.
Shoot him!

04:40.652 --> 04:41.786
Please!

04:41.903 --> 04:44.121
[gunfire outside]

04:44.206 --> 04:45.489
[sighs]
Oh. No.

04:48.160 --> 04:49.710
Ugh!

04:49.828 --> 04:50.911
[gunshot]

04:50.996 --> 04:52.263
[gasps]

04:53.137 --> 04:54.810
_

04:55.050 --> 04:56.083
[grunts]

04:56.168 --> 04:58.002
[impact]

04:58.136 --> 05:01.005
[grunting]

05:04.059 --> 05:06.010
[panting]

05:06.178 --> 05:07.144
You're all right.

05:07.262 --> 05:08.596
You're gonna be okay.

05:08.730 --> 05:10.514
(Rebecca)
You have to hold the position.

05:10.649 --> 05:12.433
Everyone's counting on us.

05:12.567 --> 05:14.602
[gasps]
And...

05:14.736 --> 05:16.787
whatever you do...

05:16.855 --> 05:19.190
don't...

05:21.026 --> 05:22.410
Don't...

05:22.527 --> 05:25.413
[somber music]

05:25.530 --> 05:30.201
♪ ♪

05:30.335 --> 05:32.119
[enraged grunt]

05:32.204 --> 05:33.704
Aah!

05:33.839 --> 05:36.957
[gunfire]

05:37.092 --> 05:38.459
Aah!

05:38.593 --> 05:40.378
[gunfire]

05:40.512 --> 05:41.879
(young Nolan)
Aah!

05:41.963 --> 05:44.265
Tell me.

05:44.383 --> 05:45.549
I won't.

05:45.717 --> 05:46.717
(young Nolan)
Aah, come on!

05:46.802 --> 05:48.185
I won't.

05:48.270 --> 05:50.604
[Nolan sobbing]

05:50.722 --> 05:51.856
[panting]

05:51.973 --> 05:53.691
I promise I won't.

05:53.809 --> 05:57.478
[mumbling]

05:57.562 --> 06:00.481
[dramatic music]

06:00.615 --> 06:08.489
♪ ♪

06:10.203 --> 06:15.203
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

06:16.472 --> 06:17.477
[glass shattering]

06:17.513 --> 06:19.878
One single task:
kill the Omec.

06:19.936 --> 06:23.054
I poisoned him with enough
zwimbo to kill a bell beast.

06:23.171 --> 06:24.755
But is the Omec dead?
No.

06:24.923 --> 06:26.807
He's at home smelling my wife
on his fingers

06:26.925 --> 06:29.176
and chuckling about how
he cuckolded the Datak Tarr!

06:29.261 --> 06:30.978
I doubt T'evgin knows your name.

06:31.096 --> 06:36.067
Incompetence is not a word
I normally associate with you.

06:36.168 --> 06:38.402
Well, perhaps there's something
deeper going on here.

06:38.520 --> 06:40.404
Deeper?
What's that supposed to mean?

06:40.522 --> 06:41.939
[Luke crying]

06:42.023 --> 06:43.991
And now look what you've done,
you've...

06:44.109 --> 06:45.993
you've woken the baby.

06:46.111 --> 06:48.412
Hello, wee one!

06:48.530 --> 06:49.680
Aww.

06:49.716 --> 06:54.803
_

06:54.838 --> 06:58.050
_

06:58.213 --> 06:59.684
That's beneath you.

07:00.058 --> 07:07.184
_

07:07.219 --> 07:12.275
_

07:12.508 --> 07:14.555
Have you quite finished?

07:14.639 --> 07:18.476
Was there more
you wanted to say?

07:18.610 --> 07:20.978
Shooting the Omec
is a stupid plan.

07:21.062 --> 07:24.064
Why is that?

07:24.199 --> 07:27.952
I learned that Omec
become stronger as they age.

07:28.036 --> 07:31.489
T'evgin is much, much older
than he appears.

07:31.623 --> 07:34.325
I doubt a sniper bullet will
do more than irritate him.

07:34.493 --> 07:36.494
Well, I'm happy to put that
theory to a test.

07:36.628 --> 07:38.913
An irritated Omec is likely to
hunt you down,

07:38.997 --> 07:40.131
hang you from your ankles,

07:40.215 --> 07:41.932
and separate you
from your spinal column.

07:42.017 --> 07:44.318
I'd like to see him try.

07:44.402 --> 07:46.320
As would I.

07:49.211 --> 07:50.691
But it won't help Alak.

07:50.826 --> 07:52.860
How does any of this help Alak?

07:55.094 --> 07:56.997
Rahm Tak is Casti.

07:57.082 --> 08:00.835
He was raised on the same old
enchanter stories we were.

08:00.919 --> 08:05.706
He fears T'evgin, which is why
he ordered us to kill him.

08:05.841 --> 08:09.176
If I can get T'evgin
on our side,

08:09.261 --> 08:12.763
we can exploit that fear to
secure Alak's release.

08:12.881 --> 08:15.549
Why would T'evgin help us?

08:15.634 --> 08:17.718
Must I draw you a chart?

08:17.853 --> 08:19.987
Contrary to what you think,
darling,

08:20.088 --> 08:21.722
your chivo is not magic.

08:21.823 --> 08:26.894
On many occasions
you've said different.

08:27.028 --> 08:29.897
You have to trust me.

08:32.508 --> 08:35.236
Of course.

08:35.301 --> 08:37.602
Always.

08:41.543 --> 08:43.126
Aah.

08:43.245 --> 08:46.130
[panting]

08:51.336 --> 08:52.503
[man shouting in the distance]

08:52.587 --> 08:53.778
Aah!

08:53.814 --> 08:56.649
[panting]

08:57.526 --> 08:59.326
_

09:01.000 --> 09:07.074
Learn the unknown English words
of this movie at www.skeebdo.com

09:09.604 --> 09:12.439
[suspenseful music]

09:12.607 --> 09:20.447
♪ ♪

09:27.660 --> 09:30.174
(Geeze) Favi Tak!
The gun seller has arrived.

09:30.325 --> 09:31.792
(Rahm) Finally.
Welcome.

09:31.960 --> 09:33.851
Your reputation precedes you,
of course.

09:33.898 --> 09:36.680
I am General Rahm Tak of
the Votanis Collective.

09:36.798 --> 09:39.133
These are Lieutenants
Bebe, Geeze.

09:39.267 --> 09:40.031
Pleasure.

09:40.067 --> 09:43.020
Please, join me
for some wine.

09:47.037 --> 09:49.727
Back to work.

09:49.811 --> 09:52.730
Yes, boss.

09:52.847 --> 09:55.733
[grunting]

09:55.867 --> 09:58.736
[dark music]

09:58.870 --> 10:00.955
♪ ♪

10:01.072 --> 10:03.324
[electronic beeping]

10:03.425 --> 10:04.425
How bad is it?

10:04.542 --> 10:05.709
He needs a machine to breathe,

10:05.860 --> 10:06.994
and I'm keeping his heart
beating with drugs.

10:07.078 --> 10:09.713
And he's not responding to
painful stimuli.

10:09.831 --> 10:11.632
Essentially,
he's brain dead.

10:11.750 --> 10:13.217
Is this true?

10:13.335 --> 10:14.918
It seems that way.

10:15.053 --> 10:16.670
You're asking
Dr. Dolittle?

10:16.805 --> 10:18.889
Suddenly my word
not good enough?

10:19.007 --> 10:20.174
I just want to make sure
everything possible

10:20.308 --> 10:22.343
is being done
to save his life.

10:22.427 --> 10:24.178
Wait, what's going on?

10:24.262 --> 10:27.014
Amanda's afraid that
I might try to kill Nolan.

10:27.148 --> 10:28.649
Why the hell would you do that?

10:28.733 --> 10:30.851
Well, because a couple weeks ago
the two of them

10:30.986 --> 10:34.021
held me down and
skinned me alive.

10:34.105 --> 10:35.406
[scoffs]

10:35.523 --> 10:37.858
Come on,
you're... you're kidding, right?

10:37.942 --> 10:40.361
That didn't... happen.

10:41.936 --> 10:43.580
You're hazing me, right?

10:43.698 --> 10:45.115
Welcome to the suck,
jarhead.

10:45.200 --> 10:46.116
[device pinging]

10:46.251 --> 10:47.918
Whoa, hang on.
Look at this.

10:48.036 --> 10:49.703
[pinging]

10:49.838 --> 10:51.622
- Brain activity.
- Out of nowhere.

10:51.756 --> 10:53.040
And it's not human.

10:53.208 --> 10:56.043
There's a mass in Nolan's
medial temporal lobe.

10:56.211 --> 10:57.428
I think it's arktech.

10:57.545 --> 10:58.946
How is that possible?

10:59.047 --> 11:00.881
It's got to be from the sleeper
pod that he shared with Irisa.

11:01.016 --> 11:03.183
She's got a scar just like this.

11:03.268 --> 11:05.185
[pings]

11:05.303 --> 11:06.654
I've got a theory.

11:06.771 --> 11:07.971
Get Irisa in here.

11:08.106 --> 11:09.390
Yeah, but I don't know
where she is.

11:09.557 --> 11:11.809
Well, if you want a shot at
saving Nolan, find her.

11:11.943 --> 11:13.460
Now!

11:16.448 --> 11:19.366
[dramatic music]

11:19.484 --> 11:27.374
♪ ♪

11:39.774 --> 11:42.359
Hey.
Have you seen Irisa?

11:45.496 --> 11:48.949
We're not exactly
soul sisters these days.

11:49.116 --> 11:52.252
Well, we have to find her
or Nolan's gonna die.

11:53.788 --> 11:56.623
[dark music]

11:56.791 --> 11:59.459
♪ ♪

11:59.627 --> 12:04.214
<i>Shtak, shtak,</i> shtak.
Where did you go?

12:04.365 --> 12:12.222
♪ ♪

12:30.791 --> 12:33.043
Help me.

12:33.160 --> 12:35.128
- How did you know?
- Just help me.

12:41.137 --> 12:43.086
I'm sorry about Rebecca.

12:43.220 --> 12:46.006
I don't want to talk about it.

12:46.090 --> 12:47.591
(Irisa)
She seemed like she really...

12:47.725 --> 12:49.676
I said I don't want to
talk about it.

12:54.914 --> 12:57.067
- Should've been me that died.
- Don't say that.

12:57.184 --> 13:00.604
She shouldn't have even
been there.

13:00.738 --> 13:04.190
I thought the war would
help me prove something.

13:04.358 --> 13:09.496
Make me a man,
or something romantic like that.

13:09.614 --> 13:13.416
Then I got there, the reality
was anything but romantic

13:13.534 --> 13:16.453
or noble, or even good.

13:16.587 --> 13:18.204
[sighs]

13:18.339 --> 13:22.042
Rebecca knew it would
be like that.

13:22.176 --> 13:25.378
So she enlisted, she made sure
she was assigned to my unit

13:25.513 --> 13:27.097
so she could protect me.

13:27.214 --> 13:28.348
She was brave.

13:28.466 --> 13:32.218
She didn't care
what anyone else thought.

13:32.303 --> 13:34.187
She was the type of girl
who'd rather be

13:34.305 --> 13:39.309
under a car fixing it than
in the backseat with a guy.

13:39.443 --> 13:41.111
All her friends loved
Taylor Swift,

13:41.228 --> 13:43.396
but she lived for
Johnny Cash.

13:46.706 --> 13:49.502
There was nothing about her
I didn't wanna be.

13:53.290 --> 13:58.128
If I had been stronger,
she'd be alive.

13:58.245 --> 13:59.779
(TV commentator)
It's been exactly one year since

13:59.914 --> 14:02.132
the fateful night that turned
the tide of the Pale Wars.

14:02.249 --> 14:05.585
The night when every alien ship
all over the world exploded.

14:05.670 --> 14:06.586
Many crashed to Earth...

14:06.671 --> 14:07.971
When are we?

14:08.089 --> 14:09.255
This is The Shaming Rack.

14:09.390 --> 14:10.423
[rock music playing]

14:10.591 --> 14:12.976
A Storm Divide watering hole.

14:13.094 --> 14:15.595
(TV commentator) Making space travel
an impossibility.

14:15.763 --> 14:17.564
The majority of the wreckage
remained in orbit

14:17.682 --> 14:19.733
and was dubbed the Ark Belt.

14:19.817 --> 14:22.335
The tragic event could not have
come at a more opportune time

14:22.436 --> 14:23.970
for the Earth military
coalition,

14:24.105 --> 14:26.489
since they were in danger of
losing the war one year ago.

14:26.607 --> 14:29.075
This is the one year anniversary
of Arkfall.

14:29.193 --> 14:32.612
Every human I knew
got plastered this night.

14:32.747 --> 14:34.447
(TV announcer) We spoke to EMC ambassador
Olfin Tennety,

14:34.582 --> 14:36.750
and here is what she had to say.

14:36.867 --> 14:39.786
Over the last year, one thing
has become clear:

14:39.920 --> 14:43.673
we have broken the back of
the Votanis Collective.

14:43.791 --> 14:46.843
They are not longer capable of
maintaining their war effort,

14:46.961 --> 14:49.062
and this has forced them
to the bargaining table.

14:49.180 --> 14:51.631
- [slam]
- War is over!

14:51.766 --> 14:53.299
- [cheering and whistling]
- Yeah!

14:53.434 --> 14:56.519
(Tennety)
To quote a great Earth leader,

14:56.637 --> 14:58.138
"Peace is at hand."

14:58.272 --> 15:00.173
Not soon enough for this guy,
huh?

15:00.307 --> 15:02.192
[chuckles]
Too true.

15:02.309 --> 15:03.727
I miss you on the front lines,
No-Man.

15:03.861 --> 15:05.145
- Oh.
- How you been paying the bills?

15:05.229 --> 15:07.280
Mm. You know how
some of that ark wreckage

15:07.364 --> 15:10.066
still falls from space to Earth?

15:10.201 --> 15:13.737
This guy Varis pays top dollar
for arktech.

15:13.821 --> 15:16.206
(J-Turk) So you're one of those scavenger
guys with a little girl in tow?

15:16.323 --> 15:19.242
The official term is arkhunter,
my friend, and the kid loves it.

15:19.376 --> 15:22.378
Right? She can climb into all
the tiny spaces I can't reach.

15:22.496 --> 15:25.048
Watch out, folks, father of
the year coming through, huh?

15:25.166 --> 15:27.217
Hey!
I'm not her dad.

15:27.334 --> 15:30.303
I just helped her out
of a bad situation.

15:30.421 --> 15:31.755
[cell phone chimes]

15:31.889 --> 15:33.339
Ooh! Arkfall.
I gotta go.

15:33.474 --> 15:34.607
I'll settle up.

15:34.725 --> 15:35.925
No, you got
the last one, J-Turk.

15:36.060 --> 15:38.511
I got this one.
Mm.

15:38.596 --> 15:41.181
[indistinct bar chatter]

15:41.315 --> 15:43.016
[Irath groans]

15:47.354 --> 15:48.988
Earth is for humans!

15:49.073 --> 15:50.523
- Yeah!
- Whoo!

15:50.691 --> 15:53.076
[rock music continues]

15:53.194 --> 15:54.410
See ya, brother.

15:54.528 --> 16:00.617
♪ ♪

16:00.701 --> 16:04.254
I have no memory of this night.

16:04.371 --> 16:06.122
Did it really happen?

16:06.257 --> 16:08.875
- Kiddo...
- Don't "kiddo" me.

16:09.043 --> 16:11.594
Did it happen?

16:11.712 --> 16:14.214
It was a different time.

16:14.381 --> 16:17.217
[whispers echoing]

16:21.972 --> 16:24.891
[dramatic music]

16:25.025 --> 16:26.292
♪ ♪

16:27.444 --> 16:29.062
[electronic beeping]

16:29.163 --> 16:30.313
Hmm.

16:30.397 --> 16:33.566
Well, the daily special seems to
be scrambled brains.

16:33.701 --> 16:34.868
What?

16:34.985 --> 16:36.486
There's an arktech cluster
in Irisa's head,

16:36.620 --> 16:38.171
just like Nolan's.

16:38.239 --> 16:39.372
And you want to know the kicker?

16:39.507 --> 16:40.406
The minute you
brought her in here,

16:40.574 --> 16:41.908
both their vitals stabilized.

16:42.076 --> 16:43.576
And Nolan's breathing
on his own.

16:43.677 --> 16:44.577
That's good, right?

16:44.745 --> 16:45.879
That means
they're getting better.

16:45.963 --> 16:49.048
Actually it's bad.
Very bad.

16:49.133 --> 16:52.836
Votan sleeper pods were not
designed for humans.

16:52.920 --> 16:55.638
Sharing one forced the pod to
make some modifications

16:55.756 --> 16:57.557
to keep if from
killing Nolan.

16:57.675 --> 16:59.058
What modifications?

16:59.176 --> 17:02.312
The pod physically tethered
Nolan and Irisa's brains.

17:02.429 --> 17:05.531
Kept them both alive, but
the brains grew interdependent,

17:05.598 --> 17:10.653
like... organs on
conjoined human twins.

17:10.771 --> 17:14.523
Right, both twins can survive,
so long as they remain attached.

17:14.608 --> 17:16.242
Exactly.

17:16.327 --> 17:18.111
The Omec severed
the attachment,

17:18.279 --> 17:20.747
when it took Nolan and Irisa
out of the pod.

17:20.848 --> 17:24.166
Now the arktech adapted itself,
keeping the connection going

17:24.285 --> 17:27.086
through a spread-spectrum
signal.

17:27.171 --> 17:29.455
Like Bluetooth?

17:29.557 --> 17:31.457
You're adorable.

17:31.542 --> 17:36.596
But sure, why not, let's call it
"Bluetooth for the brain."

17:36.714 --> 17:40.466
When you and Nolan left town,
the connection broke.

17:40.601 --> 17:44.804
But instead of a dropped signal,
they got brain damage.

17:44.972 --> 17:48.191
Bringing them closer together
reestablished the link,

17:48.309 --> 17:50.476
and stabilized their conditions.

17:50.611 --> 17:53.146
But unfortunately,
it is temporary.

17:53.280 --> 17:55.315
The arktech is growing
out of control.

17:55.449 --> 17:58.067
What can we do
to save their lives?

17:58.202 --> 18:01.738
Well, I need to open them up
and cut the arktech out.

18:01.872 --> 18:03.823
Well, you've done
this surgery before, right?

18:03.958 --> 18:06.993
Best not to dwell on that.

18:07.127 --> 18:08.027
[sighs]

18:09.496 --> 18:11.881
[panting]

18:11.999 --> 18:14.417
My hands are freezing,
I can barely hold the axe.

18:14.551 --> 18:15.718
Just give me a second
to warm them.

18:15.836 --> 18:16.719
- On your feet, let's go.
- Just give me a second

18:16.837 --> 18:18.388
to warm them, man!

18:18.505 --> 18:19.389
[knife strikes]

18:19.506 --> 18:22.392
[gurgling]

18:25.729 --> 18:28.598
[suspenseful music]

18:28.732 --> 18:36.606
♪ ♪

18:40.110 --> 18:42.724
(Rahm) Bebe, Geeze, let's start
unloading these crates.

18:42.794 --> 18:44.818
(Geeze) Favi Tak. Good news
with our guest?

18:44.854 --> 18:48.064
(Rahm) Oh, he won't stop talking,
or drinking my wine.

18:48.100 --> 18:49.339
Right now, he and his Biomen

18:49.375 --> 18:52.755
are subjecting the men
to old-earth show tunes.

18:52.873 --> 18:55.208
He's the most disgusting human
I've ever encountered,

18:55.376 --> 18:57.627
and trust me,
I've been around.

18:57.745 --> 19:01.097
He would sell his weaponry to
anyone who has enough scrip.

19:01.215 --> 19:03.850
No honor, no loyalty
to his fellow humans.

19:03.934 --> 19:07.387
I'm tempted to kill him just to
make the planet a better place.

19:07.471 --> 19:09.605
I'll deliver
the death stroke myself.

19:09.723 --> 19:12.308
That's kind of you, Bebe.
Thank you.

19:12.443 --> 19:14.477
(Rahm) No.
We may need to re-supply.

19:14.561 --> 19:17.146
It's better if he leaves with a
fat profit and we get our guns.

19:17.231 --> 19:19.899
Defiance won't know
what hit them.

19:20.067 --> 19:22.652
Don't gloat, Geeze.
It's premature.

19:22.736 --> 19:24.654
A lot of things have to go right
for this plan to work,

19:24.788 --> 19:26.205
including the element
of surprise.

19:26.323 --> 19:28.241
That's essential.

19:28.375 --> 19:30.209
I need to get back.
[sighs]

19:30.327 --> 19:34.547
I'm gonna find out if the
carnivorous plant eats Audrey.

19:34.665 --> 19:36.916
♪ ♪

19:38.926 --> 19:41.878
[indistinct chatter]

19:43.118 --> 19:45.954
[both panting and moaning]

19:58.467 --> 19:59.968
What's wrong?

20:00.004 --> 20:03.137
I'm sorry.

20:03.173 --> 20:05.272
I thought this would be
a welcome diversion,

20:05.308 --> 20:10.395
but my thoughts drift to my son
in that V.C. camp.

20:10.828 --> 20:15.832
My husband insists I carry out
their demands.

20:16.334 --> 20:19.125
Do you really believe my death
would win his release?

20:19.161 --> 20:23.217
I fear nothing short of
a miracle will save him.

20:23.253 --> 20:24.826
It's strange.

20:24.910 --> 20:31.666
When I close my eyes, I can only
picture Alak as a little boy.

20:31.800 --> 20:34.383
I keep remembering
this one day.

20:34.446 --> 20:37.805
The humans have this ancient
ritual called a picnic.

20:37.923 --> 20:39.340
Have you run across
the term yet?

20:39.425 --> 20:41.175
No.

20:41.235 --> 20:44.479
You eat outdoors among
the flies and rodents.

20:44.597 --> 20:47.515
Alak was very young
and insisted we try it.

20:47.650 --> 20:51.319
I confess it was fun
in a dirty way.

20:51.437 --> 20:54.656
Until we encountered
a hellbug skitterling.

20:54.740 --> 20:58.076
Alak thought it was cute
and wanted to play with it.

20:58.193 --> 21:02.196
But I grabbed him in my arms
and I ran.

21:02.364 --> 21:05.033
My husband tackled the beast.

21:05.167 --> 21:08.369
Killed it with his charge blade.

21:08.454 --> 21:09.754
Impressive.

21:09.872 --> 21:16.377
I held my son close, and
I whispered over and over again,

21:16.545 --> 21:21.382
"I've got you.
I will always protect you."

21:24.425 --> 21:29.390
Now I realize
that was a lie.

21:29.475 --> 21:32.560
I wish someone will give
Rahm Tak the same treatment

21:32.728 --> 21:38.149
my husband gave that hellbug.

21:38.283 --> 21:41.452
Someone strong.

21:41.570 --> 21:43.571
Someone fearless.

21:43.706 --> 21:46.741
[chuckles]
Someone like me.

21:46.909 --> 21:49.077
[laughs softly]

21:49.161 --> 21:53.414
It would be so easy for you.

21:53.549 --> 22:00.471
The sight of an Omec ship over
their camp would terrify them.

22:00.589 --> 22:03.508
They would submit
to any demand.

22:03.592 --> 22:05.510
[laughs]
Or they, being resourceful

22:05.594 --> 22:11.432
and duplicitous, would concoct
some trick to disable my ship.

22:11.600 --> 22:15.903
We could take
precautionary steps.

22:16.005 --> 22:18.773
Kindzi and I are alone.

22:18.907 --> 22:22.577
We face the extinction
of our entire race.

22:22.661 --> 22:25.113
Our only hope of finding
other Omec survivors

22:25.247 --> 22:27.498
is with that ship.

22:27.616 --> 22:30.201
I would not do anything to
put it in harm's way.

22:30.285 --> 22:32.253
Not even for you.

22:39.461 --> 22:41.963
[sighs]

22:42.097 --> 22:44.966
Seems the mood has soured.

22:49.855 --> 22:52.724
[devices pinging]

22:57.479 --> 22:58.379
[device whirring]

22:58.480 --> 23:01.449
Hmm.
We've got a problem.

23:01.533 --> 23:03.505
What?

23:03.541 --> 23:05.861
Every time I remove a piece of
arktech from Nolan's brain,

23:05.897 --> 23:09.323
the arktech in Irisa's brain
grows larger to compensate.

23:09.458 --> 23:11.492
I need to figure out a way
of removing the arktech

23:11.528 --> 23:14.328
from both of their brains
at the exact same time.

23:14.413 --> 23:17.081
Okay, well we have two doctors,

23:17.216 --> 23:20.902
so we could do two surgeries
at the same time.

23:21.003 --> 23:22.170
What do you say, slick?

23:22.337 --> 23:25.139
Any experience doing
cranial nano-surgery?

23:25.224 --> 23:30.428
Well, I... I once removed a tumor
from a cat's brain.

23:30.512 --> 23:35.183
And it lived... for, like,
a year and half.

23:35.317 --> 23:37.101
Talk about healing hands.

23:37.186 --> 23:39.937
All right, fine.
What other options do we have?

23:40.022 --> 23:42.240
Well, I need a surgery module,
one that would allow me

23:42.357 --> 23:45.993
to operate on two patients
with one set of hands.

23:46.078 --> 23:47.361
Okay, well, where can we
get one of these?

23:47.529 --> 23:49.163
Nowhere close.

23:49.281 --> 23:51.249
But I'm pretty sure
that I can make one.

23:51.366 --> 23:53.284
All I need is an Omec drone.

23:56.455 --> 23:58.422
Is that a problem?

23:59.515 --> 24:00.996
_

24:01.186 --> 24:03.739
_

24:04.046 --> 24:05.213
Where's your father?

24:05.297 --> 24:08.216
He left,
and did not tell me where.

24:08.383 --> 24:10.518
Leave this place or
I will make you leave.

24:10.602 --> 24:13.471
Nolan and Irisa will both die
if you turn us away.

24:13.555 --> 24:15.723
Please, remember,
Nolan fought for you.

24:15.808 --> 24:16.891
He saved your life.

24:17.059 --> 24:19.026
Because of gunshot wounds
inflicted by you.

24:19.111 --> 24:20.645
Don't punish him
for my mistakes.

24:20.729 --> 24:22.230
What is it you need?

24:22.364 --> 24:25.032
If I can interface
with one of your drones,

24:25.117 --> 24:27.235
it can perform one surgery
while I do the other.

24:27.369 --> 24:29.403
And steal our technology,
no doubt.

24:29.538 --> 24:32.123
Is that your plan,
crafty little Indogene?

24:32.241 --> 24:33.624
Do you play both sides?

24:33.742 --> 24:35.493
See, Mandy and I
have this bet going...

24:35.577 --> 24:37.245
Doc, shut up.

24:37.379 --> 24:39.497
Please, Kindzi.

24:42.000 --> 24:44.418
I can't lose him.

24:49.610 --> 24:52.393
I will help you.

24:52.511 --> 24:54.145
But then the scales
are balanced.

24:54.263 --> 24:55.680
We owe you people nothing.

24:55.814 --> 24:57.598
Understood.

24:57.683 --> 25:01.769
Remember this, Indogene,
I am a skilled techno-biologist.

25:01.904 --> 25:04.772
You try anything tricky when
you're connected to my system,

25:04.907 --> 25:07.491
I will see it,
and I will kill you quickly.

25:07.609 --> 25:11.112
Now, see, I was gonna
kill you slowly.

25:11.196 --> 25:13.281
I like a little bit
of foreplay.

25:13.415 --> 25:16.284
[dark music]

25:16.385 --> 25:18.619
Shall we get started,
ladies?

25:18.754 --> 25:26.627
♪ ♪

25:36.795 --> 25:37.972
[gasps]

25:38.106 --> 25:45.980
♪ ♪

25:49.952 --> 25:51.152
[exhales]

25:56.825 --> 26:00.244
[sighs]

26:02.414 --> 26:05.299
♪ ♪

26:05.417 --> 26:08.252
Here, Spot.
Come to mama.

26:08.387 --> 26:11.255
[electrical buzzing]

26:20.517 --> 26:23.184
Good ball.

26:23.268 --> 26:26.187
[stirring music]

26:26.321 --> 26:34.195
♪ ♪

26:42.029 --> 26:44.455
So far, so good.

26:53.308 --> 26:55.716
Why did you keep me
if you hated us so much?

26:55.801 --> 26:58.653
Because when I looked at you, I
didn't see an enemy combatant.

26:58.720 --> 27:01.973
I saw a scared kid
who needed my help.

27:02.057 --> 27:03.858
Besides, you were different.

27:03.976 --> 27:05.893
Different how?

27:06.028 --> 27:08.145
Well, you were born on Earth.

27:08.230 --> 27:12.066
You weren't like the Votans
we fought in the war.

27:12.234 --> 27:16.787
Are you saying you adopted me
because I wasn't alien enough to hate?

27:16.905 --> 27:19.907
- No.
- Because I am a Votan.

27:20.075 --> 27:22.243
No different from
the millions that died.

27:22.377 --> 27:23.494
Yeah.

27:23.612 --> 27:27.631
But you were too young
to experience the horror.

27:27.749 --> 27:31.969
You never saw the years of
the worst of the Pale Wars.

27:32.087 --> 27:34.989
Please don't kill me.
I don't want to die.

27:35.090 --> 27:37.008
He came after us because of
the bounty on our heads.

27:37.092 --> 27:39.093
Please, I have a family.

27:39.261 --> 27:40.311
What is this?

27:40.429 --> 27:42.146
I'll tell people
that I never found you.

27:42.264 --> 27:45.316
I don't think we're seeing
these things randomly.

27:45.434 --> 27:47.301
A lot of scrip
if he brings us in.

27:47.436 --> 27:49.804
You think he's just gonna
give up and go away?

27:50.443 --> 27:51.178
_

27:53.070 --> 27:54.825
Let me go.

27:57.779 --> 27:58.913
[sighs]

27:59.014 --> 28:01.115
Dead guy over here?

28:01.216 --> 28:02.750
He called him "odolo."

28:02.884 --> 28:04.385
(young Nolan)
It's Casti for "brother."

28:04.519 --> 28:06.854
He's honor-bound to
avenge his family.

28:06.988 --> 28:09.874
There's no way he's gonna
pack it up and go home.

28:09.958 --> 28:12.493
So maybe one night
he comes up on us,

28:12.594 --> 28:15.463
slits our throats,
is that what you want?

28:15.597 --> 28:17.715
No.

28:17.849 --> 28:21.802
So what do we do?

28:21.937 --> 28:24.105
Follow through?

28:24.222 --> 28:25.723
Follow through.

28:31.563 --> 28:34.482
[dramatic music]

28:34.616 --> 28:42.490
♪ ♪

28:49.024 --> 28:52.833
Casti heart's on
the other side.

28:52.869 --> 28:53.441
♪ ♪

28:53.477 --> 28:55.610
_

28:56.180 --> 28:58.976
_

28:59.594 --> 29:06.077
_

29:06.481 --> 29:07.598
[gunshot]

29:11.388 --> 29:13.687
I know that wasn't easy
for you, kid.

29:13.822 --> 29:16.157
I'm proud of you.

29:16.241 --> 29:18.526
All right, so let's get
this roller packed up

29:18.660 --> 29:20.277
and get out of here.

29:25.333 --> 29:28.235
[poignant music]

29:28.370 --> 29:32.106
♪ ♪

29:32.207 --> 29:34.091
I'm sorry.

29:34.209 --> 29:40.764
♪ ♪

29:40.800 --> 29:43.443
Don't tell me
I didn't grow up with horror.

29:50.814 --> 29:54.350
[whirring]

29:54.484 --> 29:57.319
[suspenseful music]

29:57.487 --> 30:00.956
♪ ♪

30:01.057 --> 30:02.458
(Datak)
Come on.

30:02.575 --> 30:04.159
Move.

30:04.294 --> 30:07.129
Or I'll do you both.

30:07.213 --> 30:10.499
I want you to know that
I understand.

30:10.583 --> 30:14.136
You have to put
your own family first.

30:14.254 --> 30:15.754
I appreciate that.

30:23.966 --> 30:26.835
[speaking native language]

30:33.073 --> 30:34.823
[laughs]

30:34.941 --> 30:36.325
[slight laugh]

30:36.409 --> 30:39.194
Have you tried
pow vindaloo yet?

30:39.329 --> 30:40.496
No.

30:40.580 --> 30:43.248
You are in for a treat.

30:43.366 --> 30:44.717
This way.

30:52.833 --> 30:54.082
_

30:59.573 --> 31:01.216
Alak!

31:01.351 --> 31:03.218
Why are you unattended?

31:03.353 --> 31:06.388
I-I begged Sagyan for a break.

31:06.556 --> 31:08.190
I couldn't take
the smell of those bodies.

31:08.274 --> 31:11.393
Well, I'm gonna have to talk
with Sagyan about his leniency.

31:11.478 --> 31:14.563
It's odd, though,
the smell bothers you.

31:14.698 --> 31:18.133
You were married to a human.

31:18.234 --> 31:19.234
I'm curious.

31:19.319 --> 31:21.403
Did you have to
scrub really hard

31:21.488 --> 31:23.872
to get the smell
off your <i>gwavayo?</i>

31:23.957 --> 31:26.825
[laughs]

31:26.960 --> 31:28.877
[gunshot]

31:28.995 --> 31:31.747
Agh!

31:31.915 --> 31:33.165
[groaning]

31:33.299 --> 31:34.883
[suspenseful music]

31:34.984 --> 31:36.251
[engine starts]

31:36.419 --> 31:39.471
♪ ♪

31:39.589 --> 31:42.474
[gunfire]

31:48.898 --> 31:50.866
[laughs]

32:08.258 --> 32:11.003
I know this place.

32:11.121 --> 32:12.454
I'm sorry.

32:12.622 --> 32:14.423
What?

32:14.507 --> 32:17.159
About the bounty hunter.

32:17.260 --> 32:21.130
I didn't know it
affected you so much.

32:21.214 --> 32:23.298
I'm not sorry for the lesson,
though.

32:23.433 --> 32:24.850
You would've been dead years ago

32:24.968 --> 32:27.636
if I hadn't taught you
how to survive.

32:41.317 --> 32:44.203
[dramatic music]

32:44.320 --> 32:52.211
♪ ♪

32:59.241 --> 33:00.502
[can crunches]

33:00.637 --> 33:02.805
[inhales]

33:02.906 --> 33:06.341
[groans]
Hi, kiddo.

33:06.509 --> 33:07.726
What's wrong,
you can't sleep?

33:07.844 --> 33:09.595
Too cold?

33:09.729 --> 33:11.013
Come on up.

33:11.147 --> 33:12.681
Come on, up here.

33:14.719 --> 33:17.519
Ah, that's it.

33:17.654 --> 33:19.521
Good.

33:32.836 --> 33:33.919
Was that real?

33:34.037 --> 33:35.671
Something's happening.

33:35.755 --> 33:37.406
Was it real?
Did it actually happen?

33:37.540 --> 33:39.424
Thought about it.

33:39.542 --> 33:40.542
I don't believe you.

33:40.710 --> 33:41.844
Believe what you want.

33:41.928 --> 33:43.795
No, I remember that night.

33:43.880 --> 33:45.214
That was the first time
I thought everything

33:45.348 --> 33:46.465
was gonna be okay.

33:46.549 --> 33:49.251
It was the first time we started
to feel like a family.

33:49.352 --> 33:50.385
It happened.

33:50.520 --> 33:51.887
Why?

33:52.021 --> 33:54.306
Because I was scared of you.

33:54.390 --> 33:56.642
I was scared of you.

33:58.194 --> 34:01.063
[rumbling]

34:03.260 --> 34:05.567
[inhales]

34:05.702 --> 34:06.735
They're awake.

34:06.870 --> 34:08.320
Thank God.

34:08.404 --> 34:10.539
[both groaning]

34:18.748 --> 34:21.550
How are you feeling?

34:21.668 --> 34:23.969
Ugh.
Yeah.

34:24.087 --> 34:26.588
(Nolan)
Dizzy.

34:26.672 --> 34:28.306
Irisa, how are you feeling?

34:28.424 --> 34:30.092
[exhales]
<i>Shtako.</i>

34:30.226 --> 34:32.928
All right, move slow.

34:33.012 --> 34:33.929
[sighs]

34:34.063 --> 34:35.764
You scared me.

34:35.931 --> 34:38.433
I don't know what I would
have done without you.

34:38.568 --> 34:41.436
[poignant music]

34:41.603 --> 34:45.440
♪ ♪

34:47.360 --> 34:49.864
(T'evgin) You should never have allowed
them in here.

34:49.983 --> 34:51.483
Where is
this Indogene now?

34:51.618 --> 34:54.536
She took Nolan and Irisa back
to town for more tests.

34:54.654 --> 34:57.706
I should strip off your skin
and feed it to my bulel.

34:57.824 --> 35:00.409
You are my commander.
It is your prerogative.

35:00.493 --> 35:02.961
Don't you understand the danger?

35:03.079 --> 35:07.216
You allowed a shape-taker
to access our network.

35:07.367 --> 35:09.635
An Indogene!

35:09.769 --> 35:11.937
She could have seized control
of our drones.

35:12.005 --> 35:14.139
A network is
a two-way street.

35:14.257 --> 35:15.674
She was so busy
with the surgery,

35:15.808 --> 35:16.892
she failed to notice

35:17.043 --> 35:19.895
that I copied her
cerebral source-print.

35:20.013 --> 35:21.013
[inhales]

35:24.639 --> 35:25.817
You got it all?

35:25.935 --> 35:28.187
Everything.

35:28.321 --> 35:30.906
This particular shape-taker,
Yewll, is smart,

35:31.024 --> 35:32.991
even by Indogene standards.

35:33.109 --> 35:34.776
Her expertise will
prove valuable

35:34.911 --> 35:37.779
once the <i>maret adziim</i> begins.

35:37.914 --> 35:39.531
[dark music]

35:39.666 --> 35:41.867
You're very resourceful.

35:41.951 --> 35:44.119
But also reckless.

35:44.204 --> 35:46.872
Destroy it.

35:46.956 --> 35:48.624
Why?

35:48.708 --> 35:52.377
Creating new Indogenes would
turn Defiance against us.

35:52.478 --> 35:53.595
We are Omec.

35:53.713 --> 35:56.932
We feed upon the lesser races.
We do not fear them.

35:57.050 --> 36:00.385
I fear anything that will
disrupt the flow of gulanite

36:00.520 --> 36:04.389
and prevent us from
repairing the Tsuroz.

36:04.474 --> 36:07.476
You are young.

36:07.560 --> 36:10.395
Two bullets from a human
almost killed you.

36:10.480 --> 36:11.730
Have you forgotten this?

36:11.864 --> 36:14.066
I will never forget that.

36:16.069 --> 36:19.171
Follow my orders.
Destroy it.

36:19.239 --> 36:21.323
Of course, commander.

36:21.457 --> 36:26.328
♪ ♪

36:28.074 --> 36:29.748
[sighs]

36:31.801 --> 36:34.105
[indistinct shouting]

36:34.141 --> 36:36.722
[sighs]

36:36.806 --> 36:38.557
Does your head hurt?

36:38.675 --> 36:41.226
A little.

36:41.311 --> 36:43.562
I can taste something.

36:43.646 --> 36:45.013
Burnt tires?

36:45.098 --> 36:47.266
[laughs]
Yeah. That's it.

36:48.852 --> 36:51.486
So...

36:51.604 --> 36:52.821
If you're that scared of me,

36:52.939 --> 36:57.242
why didn't you just sink
the knife and be done with it?

36:57.327 --> 36:59.528
Because I'm not you.

36:59.612 --> 37:01.780
Something pulled
these memories

37:01.948 --> 37:04.366
from both our minds
to understand that.

37:04.450 --> 37:07.336
So we could both see the lie

37:07.453 --> 37:09.288
that's kept us together
for all these years.

37:09.422 --> 37:10.922
What lie?
I never lied to you.

37:11.007 --> 37:13.859
You taught me to believe
we're the same.

37:13.993 --> 37:17.012
Yeah, we both grew up
with blood in our hands.

37:17.130 --> 37:20.632
It made you okay with killing.

37:20.767 --> 37:22.851
But not me.

37:22.969 --> 37:25.962
I hated it then
and I hate it now.

37:30.329 --> 37:33.130
I think that's why
I didn't stab you.

37:35.490 --> 37:37.223
I have to leave.

37:38.534 --> 37:40.974
There's no place for me here.

37:42.746 --> 37:44.731
Not with Rahm Tak coming.

37:46.320 --> 37:48.086
If I stay,
I'll have to hurt people,

37:48.122 --> 37:51.263
and if I don't,
I'll get you killed.

37:51.299 --> 37:52.876
Don't you worry about me.

37:52.912 --> 37:55.808
You can't protect me
and the town at the same time.

37:56.352 --> 37:58.391
I know what you have to do.

38:00.151 --> 38:02.645
It takes a killer
to stop a killer.

38:03.279 --> 38:05.497
I know what you have to be,

38:05.810 --> 38:08.695
but I don't want to
be here for it.

38:11.934 --> 38:13.391
Okay.

38:18.454 --> 38:20.782
"Live together, die together."

38:21.761 --> 38:24.317
Works when you have to
keep on fighting.

38:25.622 --> 38:27.985
It totally sucks in real life.

38:28.021 --> 38:30.889
[laughter]

38:38.774 --> 38:41.511
There's a land coach
coming tomorrow.

38:44.992 --> 38:46.700
Well, you let me know
where you end up.

38:46.736 --> 38:48.133
[sighs]

38:50.072 --> 38:52.968
Maybe when this is all over
I can join you there.

38:53.564 --> 38:54.863
Maybe.

38:54.898 --> 39:05.507
♪ ♪

39:05.543 --> 39:07.543
[fire crackling]

39:10.584 --> 39:13.161
I just finished going through
your post-op scans.

39:13.228 --> 39:15.731
I didn't want to say anything
until I was sure.

39:15.832 --> 39:17.021
Sure about what?

39:17.107 --> 39:20.340
I wasn't able to remove
the arktech, so I repaired it.

39:20.376 --> 39:21.696
Strengthened to
the connection.

39:21.732 --> 39:23.205
You two will remain stable

39:23.306 --> 39:26.008
so long as you don't
separate again.

39:26.092 --> 39:27.175
Meaning?

39:27.343 --> 39:28.594
Meaning if you get
too far apart,

39:28.728 --> 39:30.729
you'll strain the connection,
excruciating pain,

39:30.880 --> 39:32.147
killing you both,
the whole magilla.

39:32.232 --> 39:34.066
How far is too far?

39:34.183 --> 39:37.653
I don't know.
A mile, maybe more.

39:37.770 --> 39:39.221
- [sighs]
- [scoffs]

39:39.355 --> 39:40.522
Why the long faces?

39:40.657 --> 39:42.741
You two are practically
joined at the hip anyway.

39:45.651 --> 39:48.697
[sighs]
"Geez, thanks, Doc Yewl,

39:48.831 --> 39:50.332
for saving us
from certain death."

39:50.450 --> 39:52.367
Hey, no problem kids,
any time.

39:52.502 --> 39:54.202
Grab a lollipop
on your way out.

39:56.793 --> 40:00.008
[dark music]

40:00.126 --> 40:05.881
♪ ♪

40:05.951 --> 40:07.883
Go away.

40:09.652 --> 40:12.321
But not too far,
obviously.

40:12.455 --> 40:20.312
♪ ♪

40:25.361 --> 40:26.952
[sighs]

40:31.860 --> 40:35.127
[soft native music playing]

40:35.244 --> 40:38.997
♪ ♪

40:39.075 --> 40:41.300
What is Rahm Tak like
in person?

40:41.417 --> 40:44.002
Excuse me?

40:44.087 --> 40:46.755
I shame myself.
The question was impertinent.

40:46.923 --> 40:49.641
No, it's all right, Andina.

40:49.759 --> 40:52.427
Why do you ask?

40:52.512 --> 40:56.064
I saw his image
the day the Arch fell.

40:56.149 --> 40:58.767
He's very handsome.

40:58.851 --> 41:01.653
Dangerous looking.

41:01.771 --> 41:04.356
Yes.

41:04.440 --> 41:08.660
I prefer my men dangerous,
don't you?

41:08.778 --> 41:11.346
Generally, they prefer me.

41:11.447 --> 41:12.748
♪ ♪

41:12.832 --> 41:14.416
Some of the other servants think

41:14.500 --> 41:17.786
humans have brought all of this
upon themselves.

41:17.920 --> 41:20.205
All of what?

41:20.289 --> 41:24.042
The righteous wrath of
the Votanis Collective.

41:24.127 --> 41:26.345
If humans had been better about
sharing their planet,

41:26.462 --> 41:28.547
then we wouldn't hate them.

41:28.631 --> 41:30.966
That's Rahm Tak's whole message.

41:31.100 --> 41:34.302
There's more to it than that.

41:37.239 --> 41:38.640
[gasps]

41:38.775 --> 41:41.643
[stirring music]

41:41.811 --> 41:48.233
♪ ♪

41:48.317 --> 41:49.670
[both scream]

41:49.763 --> 41:50.865
You... you're in shock.

41:50.920 --> 41:52.654
You killed Christie.

41:52.789 --> 41:53.760
Oh, no, no, no, I didn't...

41:53.796 --> 41:54.945
Shut your lying mouth!

41:54.981 --> 41:56.740
There's always an excuse.

41:56.776 --> 41:59.066
You've never told the truth.

41:59.102 --> 42:00.902
[whimpering]

42:01.227 --> 42:04.976
♪ Yes we'll fight now
for our funding ♪

